-- Hungary Stocks: Magyar Telekom, OTP Bank Move in Budapest Trade
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-05-03T15:43:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-03/hungary-stocks-magyar-telekom-otp-bank-move-in-budapest-trade.html
Hungary’s benchmark  BUX (BUX)  index fell 0.9
percent to 17,871.46 by the close in Budapest, retreating for a
second day.  The following are among the most active shares in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Magyar Telekom Nyrt. (MTEL)  , Hungary’s former phone
monopoly controlled by Deutsche Telekom AG, gained after news
website Index reported the government will impose monthly limits
on a planned phone tax. The shares rose as much as 0.9 percent
and last traded 0.4 percent higher at 537 forint.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender, declined
3.2 percent to 3,678 forint. Data on global jobs and China’s
services industry raised concern about slower economic growth.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
